ifacts-at-fort-ticonderoga-the-site-of-americas-first-offensive-victory-of-the-revolutionary-war-180988971/</guid></item><item><title>为庆祝其生日，美国将向未来的美国人赠送一个重达 900 磅的时间胶囊，里面装满了艺术品、自然宝藏和精美的《独立宣言》副本</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/indigenous-art-an-eagle-feather-and-a-3d-rendering-of-abraham-lincolns-hand-see-the-items-just-sealed-in-americas-time-capsule-180988973/</link><description>该胶囊是在国会的指导下通过 America250 委员会创建和填充的。它将于 7 月 4 日被埋葬在原来的雕塑下面</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 17:20:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/indigenous-art-an-eagle-feather-and-a-3d-rendering-of-abraham-lincolns-hand-see-the-items-just-sealed-in-americas-time-capsule-180988973/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚城市的雄性园丁鸟将人类垃圾变成宝藏，以打动潜在的配偶</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/male-bowerbirds-in-australian-cities-are-turning-human-trash-into-treasure-to-impress-potential-mates-180988969/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，即使是乡村鸟类在选择人造物体（例如彩色玻璃和金属丝）和自然装饰品（例如树叶和贝壳）时也更喜欢它们</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 15:35:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/male-bowerbirds-in-australian-cities-are-turning-human-trash-into-treasure-to-impress-potential-mates-180988969/</guid></item><item><title>临床试验表明，这种“改变实践”的基因测试可以告诉医生哪些乳腺癌患者可以跳过化疗</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-practice-changing-gene-test-could-tell-doctors-which-patients-with-breast-cancer-can-skip-chemo-clinical-trial-suggests-180988957/</link><description>化疗会带来使人衰弱的副作用，包括脑雾、恶心和神经损伤。新研究表明，许多患有常见类型乳腺癌的人只需要放射治疗和激素治疗即可预防复发</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 14:01:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-practice-changing-gene-test-could-tell-doctors-which-patients-with-breast-cancer-can-skip-chemo-clinical-trial-suggests-180988957/</guid></item><item><title>科学家发现了关于北爱尔兰标志性地质结构巨人堤道火山起源的新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientis